Updated Syllabus (1st part) (1/2)
Foundations of pattern recognition and machine learning:
Basic terminologies and concepts of PRML;
Bayes’ rule and univariate probability distribution models;
Maximum Likelihood Estimation (MLE)
Empirical Risk Minimization (ERM).
Decision theory and classifiers:
Bayesian decision theory and the classification problem;
Bayesian classifiers for normal distribution and Maximum A Posteriori (MAP);
The frequentist decision theory and its application.
